945
01:12:13,345 --> 01:12:17,805
He never thought of buying
things like that for himself.

946
01:12:18,950 --> 01:12:22,681
And then I stopped at
the minister's to remind him...

947
01:12:22,854 --> 01:12:26,950
<i>... that Joe and I would be there</i>
<i>at 4:00, and not to forget.</i>

948
01:12:28,527 --> 01:12:31,155
<i>We'd been away from</i>
<i>each other so long.</i>

949
01:12:31,330 --> 01:12:33,560
<i>More than a year.</i>

950
01:12:34,232 --> 01:12:38,191
<i>And l... I loved him so.</i>

951
01:13:08,667 --> 01:13:12,103
<i>I turn the witness over to the defense.</i>

952
01:13:12,471 --> 01:13:15,531
<i>Miss Grant. According to</i>
<i>the fact of psychology...</i>

953
01:13:15,707 --> 01:13:20,041
...that under great emotional stress
the mind sees what it has expected to...

954
01:13:20,212 --> 01:13:22,772
...whether the thing
is actually there or not...

955
01:13:22,981 --> 01:13:27,042
...is it not possible that you
did not see Joseph Wilson...

956
01:13:27,219 --> 01:13:31,121
...but only the image of him your
imagination had created in your head?

957
01:13:31,289 --> 01:13:34,884
No, I saw him. I saw him
burning to death there!

958
01:13:35,060 --> 01:13:38,689
You can see that picture now
too, can't you?

959
01:13:38,864 --> 01:13:41,298
- I'll always see it.
- So perhaps after all...

960
01:13:41,500 --> 01:13:45,800
...it was an hallucination of your tortured
mind that you saw there...

961
01:13:46,004 --> 01:13:48,199
...just as you see it here.

962
01:13:48,373 --> 01:13:52,070
What do you want me to say,
yes or no? I tell you I saw him.

963
01:13:52,244 --> 01:13:56,738
Can you, from your
own personal knowledge...

964
01:13:56,915 --> 01:13:59,713
...swear that Joseph Wilson is dead?

965
01:13:59,885 --> 01:14:02,445
Why, no. That is, yes.

966
01:14:02,621 --> 01:14:05,249
- I mean, one can assume.
- Excuse me...

967
01:14:05,424 --> 01:14:09,451
...but that is exactly what must not
be assumed, but proved!

968
01:14:09,628 --> 01:14:13,462
The state is asking the lives
of 22 people for one.

969
01:14:13,632 --> 01:14:15,964
I don't care about the lives of 22 people!

970
01:14:16,134 --> 01:14:18,568
They can't bring back
the life I cared about.

971
01:14:18,737 --> 01:14:23,970
I only wish I hadn't fainted. I wish I could
have gone in there to him. With him.

972
01:14:24,443 --> 01:14:26,673
That's all, Miss Grant.

973
01:14:33,985 --> 01:14:37,250
I will remind the jury
that under the law...

974
01:14:37,422 --> 01:14:41,791
...lives must not be taken on
assumptions but on facts!

975
01:14:41,960 --> 01:14:44,520
Where is the corpse of Joseph Wilson?

976
01:14:44,696 --> 01:14:48,029
<i>The law is that the corpus</i>
<i>delicti must be established...</i>

977
01:14:48,200 --> 01:14:50,327
<i>... at least by fragments</i>
<i>of the human body...</i>

978
01:14:50,502 --> 01:14:54,939
<i>... or of articles known and proved</i>
<i>to have been worn by the deceased.</i>

979
01:14:55,273 --> 01:14:58,936
And in the absence of convincing proof
of the corpus delicti...

980
01:14:59,110 --> 01:15:01,943
...I move this indictment
be wiped off the records...

981
01:15:02,147 --> 01:15:05,639
...and the charges against
these defendants be dismissed.

982
01:15:05,817 --> 01:15:09,844
I shall take the motion for dismissal
under advisement until tomorrow...

983
01:15:10,355 --> 01:15:13,017
<i>... and hear the state's arguments then.</i>

984
01:15:27,339 --> 01:15:30,069
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

985
01:15:30,242 --> 01:15:32,176
...I have received an object...

986
01:15:32,344 --> 01:15:34,209
...which, if authentic...

987
01:15:34,379 --> 01:15:37,246
...must be considered
as evidence in this case.

988
01:15:37,616 --> 01:15:42,519
As to its authenticity, I am not
permitted to have an opinion.

989
01:15:42,687 --> 01:15:46,748
However, in order to present it to you...

990
01:15:46,925 --> 01:15:49,689
...I must take the witness stand.

991
01:15:50,862 --> 01:15:52,420
Mr. Clerk...

992
01:15:52,631 --> 01:15:54,360
...please swear me.

993
01:15:59,404 --> 01:16:03,067
Do you swear that you'll tell the truth
and nothing but the truth?

994
01:16:03,241 --> 01:16:05,436
- I do.
- Please be seated.

995
01:16:07,846 --> 01:16:10,610
This is a special delivery
letter postmarked...

996
01:16:10,782 --> 01:16:14,047
...in this city at 11 p.m. Last night...

997
01:16:14,219 --> 01:16:19,350
...and addressed "Judge Daniel Hopkins,
Hall of Justice, Courtroom 10."

998
01:16:19,724 --> 01:16:22,921
Is this the letter you received,
Your Honor?

999
01:16:28,266 --> 01:16:29,893
It is.

1000
01:16:31,436 --> 01:16:34,030
The communication is not handwritten.

1001
01:16:34,205 --> 01:16:37,368
It is formed by letters cut
from a newspaper...

1002
01:16:37,542 --> 01:16:40,272
...and pasted together to spell words.

1003
01:16:40,445 --> 01:16:44,245
It is, ladies and gentlemen, the
confession of a tortured conscience.

1004
01:16:44,416 --> 01:16:45,747
Listen.

1005
01:16:45,917 --> 01:16:48,078
"I can't hide the truth any longer.

1006
01:16:48,253 --> 01:16:52,314
I am a citizen of Strand
who helped clean up the jail mess.

1007
01:16:52,490 --> 01:16:56,085
In the ashes,
I found this enclosed ring.

1008
01:16:56,261 --> 01:17:01,597
Nobody knew it, so I was keeping it for
a mement... Memento.

1009
01:17:01,766 --> 01:17:03,996
But it is upsetting my conscience.

1010
01:17:04,202 --> 01:17:08,434
I don't dare sign this, or I would
probably get lynched myself.

1011
01:17:08,607 --> 01:17:11,337
A citizen of Strand."

1012
01:17:15,480 --> 01:17:17,744
I now draw your attention to this ring.

1013
01:17:17,916 --> 01:17:22,080
It's gold, melted and misshapen,
as if by fire.

1014
01:17:22,287 --> 01:17:26,951
Inside the ring is an engraved
inscription, reading...

1015
01:17:27,158 --> 01:17:29,353
I can decipher only the words...

1016
01:17:29,527 --> 01:17:32,519
..."Henry to K."

1017
01:17:32,731 --> 01:17:34,323
The rest is melted out.

1018
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:38,231
But after that word, I can plainly read...

1019
01:17:38,436 --> 01:17:40,768
...in a different style of engraving...

1020
01:17:40,939 --> 01:17:43,305
..."To Joe," obviously meaning...

1021
01:17:43,475 --> 01:17:45,534
- Objection!
- Sustained.

1022
01:17:45,744 --> 01:17:49,009
Since when have anonymous letters
become gospel in law?

1023
01:17:49,180 --> 01:17:52,479
Who can say that ring was
the property of Joseph Wilson?

1024
01:17:52,651 --> 01:17:54,846
What proof is there that it was found...

1025
01:17:55,020 --> 01:17:58,285
...as that concocted letter
would have us believe?

1026
01:17:58,456 --> 01:18:01,823
Who sent that letter?
A man afraid to sign his name.

1027
01:18:02,327 --> 01:18:05,558
I believe that this fraud is
a fabrication of some soul...

1028
01:18:07,265 --> 01:18:10,257
...poisoned with hostility
toward these defendants!

1029
01:18:10,568 --> 01:18:14,504
The state recalls
Katherine Grant to the stand.

1030
01:18:25,016 --> 01:18:29,544
I will remind you, Miss Grant,
you've already sworn to tell the truth.

1031
01:18:30,889 --> 01:18:34,052
Have you ever seen this ring before?

1032
01:18:36,094 --> 01:18:39,325
- Yes.
- Where and when?

1033
01:18:39,998 --> 01:18:42,694
In the railroad station in Chicago.

1034
01:18:42,867 --> 01:18:45,062
When I was leaving to come here.

1035
01:18:45,236 --> 01:18:46,999
I gave it to Joe.

1036
01:18:47,172 --> 01:18:50,699
What did Joseph Wilson do with it
when you gave it to him?

1037
01:18:51,710 --> 01:18:54,110
He put it on his little finger.

1038
01:18:54,312 --> 01:18:57,008
It was too small for any other finger.

1039
01:18:57,182 --> 01:19:00,379
How can you be sure this ring
is the one you gave him...

1040
01:19:00,552 --> 01:19:03,749
...and saw him put
on his little finger there?

1041
01:19:06,324 --> 01:19:08,622
Because it was my mother's.

1042
01:19:09,227 --> 01:19:14,096
It had engraved "Henry,"
my father's name...

1043
01:19:14,766 --> 01:19:18,532
..."to Katherine," which was
my mother's name too.

1044
01:19:20,238 --> 01:19:22,729
After the "Katherine"...

1045
01:19:23,141 --> 01:19:25,609
...I had it engraved...

1046
01:19:26,377 --> 01:19:28,470
..."to Joe."

1047
01:19:30,615 --> 01:19:32,378
I want to confess!

1048
01:19:32,550 --> 01:19:34,040
Let me go!

1049
01:19:34,219 --> 01:19:35,777
I threw stones at him!

1050
01:19:35,987 --> 01:19:37,318
I helped kill him!

1051
01:19:37,489 --> 01:19:40,583
I'm guilty! We're all guilty!

1052
01:19:40,759 --> 01:19:45,162
Let me ask her to forgive me!
Please, please, forgive me!

1053
01:19:45,396 --> 01:19:46,920
Forgive me!

1054
01:19:47,098 --> 01:19:49,157
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

1055
01:19:49,367 --> 01:19:51,062
Forgive me!

1056
01:19:51,236 --> 01:19:54,069
...there is your answer to this case!

1057
01:19:56,107 --> 01:19:59,099
That letter cinched it for us, didn't it?

1058
01:20:00,078 --> 01:20:02,103
Yeah, why?

1059
01:20:02,380 --> 01:20:05,474
It was certainly lucky for us
that it showed up...

1060
01:20:05,650 --> 01:20:08,414
...wasn't it?
- Stop talking about it.

1061
01:20:08,586 --> 01:20:10,144
I mean...

1062
01:20:10,321 --> 01:20:12,687
...where does it get you?

1063
01:20:15,927 --> 01:20:18,794
- Why didn't you tell me Joe was alive?
- What?

1064
01:20:18,963 --> 01:20:21,796
- Are you crazy?
- I know he's alive, Charlie. I know.

1065
01:20:21,966 --> 01:20:23,991
Will you shut your mouth?

1066
01:20:24,536 --> 01:20:27,164
You can't keep me quiet.
What's happened to him?

1067
01:20:27,338 --> 01:20:30,603
Does he realize what he's done?
What we've all done?

1068
01:20:30,775 --> 01:20:32,640
- Where is he?
- You saw him.

1069
01:20:32,811 --> 01:20:34,802
You saw him in that fire.
Why ask me?

1070
01:20:34,979 --> 01:20:37,948
You testified, not me. I wasn't there.

1071
01:20:38,116 --> 01:20:40,812
You're losing your mind again.

1072
01:20:42,620 --> 01:20:44,611
Of course.

1073
01:20:44,989 --> 01:20:47,184
Of course you're right.

1074
01:20:49,794 --> 01:20:52,319
I don't know what's the matter with me.

1075
01:20:52,997 --> 01:20:54,828
Of course you're right.

1076
01:20:54,999 --> 01:20:56,660
He's dead.

1077
01:20:57,969 --> 01:21:01,132
But I haven't slept for so long.

1078
01:21:01,973 --> 01:21:03,964
I want to go.

1079
01:21:04,142 --> 01:21:06,702
I can't listen to any more.
I want to go home.

1080
01:21:08,680 --> 01:21:11,513
It was that letter that made her jump.
I don't know...

1081
01:21:11,683 --> 01:21:13,913
You're trying to make yourself important.

1082
01:21:14,085 --> 01:21:17,248
- Katherine suspicious? You're daffy!
- I'm daffy!

1083
01:21:17,455 --> 01:21:20,390
Take a look at your radio.
I tell you, that letter...

1084
01:21:20,558 --> 01:21:23,391
That letter was the best idea I ever had.

1085
01:21:23,561 --> 01:21:26,997
Yeah. Almost cost me my finger
getting that ring off.

1086
01:21:27,165 --> 01:21:31,465
But it was worth it. It would have been
worth the whole hand. Two hands.

1087
01:21:32,036 --> 01:21:35,233
Tom, why don't you stick with me?
You know as well...

1088
01:21:35,406 --> 01:21:38,773
Yeah, you're right.
What's the use of fighting with him?

1089
01:21:38,977 --> 01:21:42,879
Anyway, she's home now.
We got the landlady to put her to bed.

1090
01:21:43,681 --> 01:21:46,673
Must have been some sensation
when that woman collapsed.

1091
01:21:46,885 --> 01:21:49,217
They could stand seeing
me burned to death.

1092
01:21:49,387 --> 01:21:51,981
- They can't stand an honest trial.
- Cut it out!

1093
01:21:52,190 --> 01:21:54,750
I can't stand it!
I can't hear any more!

1094
01:21:54,926 --> 01:21:58,885
You haven't been watching them.
You didn't look in their eyes.

1095
01:21:59,063 --> 01:22:03,227
- Yellow-livered welsher, sorry for them.
- You're as bad! You're lynching me!

1096
01:22:03,401 --> 01:22:07,861
It's getting me too. I wish I hadn't
started the whole thing. I was with you.

1097
01:22:08,039 --> 01:22:10,701
But I got a feeling you talked
me into something.

1098
01:22:10,875 --> 01:22:12,706
If I could think of a way out...

1099
01:22:12,877 --> 01:22:14,435
Why don't you snitch on me!

1100
01:22:14,612 --> 01:22:18,742
- Nobody's talking about that!
- I am! I can't stand it any longer!

1101
01:22:19,550 --> 01:22:20,949
Be human, Joe.

1102
01:22:21,119 --> 01:22:23,383
We can get out of the country,
start over.

1103
01:22:23,554 --> 01:22:27,957
But let's tell them the truth.
Let's tell them you're alive!

1104
01:22:29,527 --> 01:22:31,893
I'll kill you first.

1105
01:22:34,432 --> 01:22:37,333
You might as well kill me too.

1106
01:22:42,407 --> 01:22:44,307
You brought her here, you lying...

1107
01:22:44,475 --> 01:22:45,942
No, Joe. I followed them!

1108
01:22:46,110 --> 01:22:50,945
I knew you were alive when I saw your
letter. Why not kill me! Do a good job!

1109
01:22:51,115 --> 01:22:55,017
What difference does it make?
Twenty-two, 23, 25!

1110
01:22:55,186 --> 01:22:57,654
- Listen to me, Joe.
- No!

1111
01:23:00,124 --> 01:23:01,853
I'm sorry.

1112
01:23:02,060 --> 01:23:04,528
I didn't mean to talk that way.

1113
01:23:04,696 --> 01:23:08,188
Joe, I understand how you feel...

1114
01:23:08,366 --> 01:23:10,834
...and I understand
why you feel that way.

1115
01:23:11,002 --> 01:23:12,970
When I thought you were dead...

1116
01:23:13,137 --> 01:23:16,368
...when I thought of what killed you,
I wanted revenge too.

1117
01:23:16,574 --> 01:23:18,132
But now I don't.

1118
01:23:18,309 --> 01:23:22,678
I want to be happy again. I want what
we've always promised each other.

1119
01:23:22,847 --> 01:23:25,816
You ought to have violins
playing when you talk.

1120
01:23:25,984 --> 01:23:29,818
- I know what I want, and I'm getting it!
- You're hanging 22 people!

1121
01:23:29,988 --> 01:23:33,287
No, I'm not. I'm hanging 22 rats
for something they did do.

1122
01:23:33,458 --> 01:23:35,289
- These are 22 human beings.
- Yeah.

1123
01:23:35,460 --> 01:23:38,623
- They live and breathe.
- Like me in the jail, for instance!

1124
01:23:38,796 --> 01:23:41,856
They're not murderers.
They were part of a mob.

1125
01:23:42,033 --> 01:23:46,367
- A mob doesn't think. It hasn't time.
- What about the guy in jail? He can think.

1126
01:23:46,537 --> 01:23:50,337
All right, it's his turn. Let them know
what it means to be lynched.

1127
01:23:50,508 --> 01:23:52,669
- Don't you think they know by now?
- No.

1128
01:23:52,844 --> 01:23:57,713
What you've felt for a few hours,
they've had to face for days and weeks!

1129
01:23:57,882 --> 01:24:02,546
Wishing, with all their souls, they could
have that one day to live over again.

1130
01:24:04,355 --> 01:24:05,879
Joe...

1131
01:24:06,824 --> 01:24:08,758
...don't you see?

1132
01:24:09,227 --> 01:24:12,196
We can be together and be happy.

1133
01:24:13,664 --> 01:24:16,360
Let me go with you to the judge.

1134
01:24:16,901 --> 01:24:19,734
And then we can start all over again.

1135
01:24:19,904 --> 01:24:22,429
Stop thinking about them.
Think about me.

1136
01:24:22,640 --> 01:24:24,835
I am thinking about you.

1137
01:24:25,009 --> 01:24:27,102
About what a swell guy you were...

1138
01:24:27,278 --> 01:24:30,338
...when you were alive.
- When I was alive?

1139
01:24:30,515 --> 01:24:33,348
If those people die, Joe Wilson dies.
You know that.

1140
01:24:33,518 --> 01:24:36,351
Wherever you go. Whatever you do.

1141
01:24:37,555 --> 01:24:39,887
I couldn't marry you now, Joe.

1142
01:24:40,191 --> 01:24:42,421
I couldn't marry a dead man.

1143
01:24:42,593 --> 01:24:45,790
All right, then, all right!
I don't need anybody!

1144
01:24:45,963 --> 01:24:47,430
Nobody!

1145
01:24:49,200 --> 01:24:51,464
Maybe this is crazy.

1146
01:24:52,804 --> 01:24:56,240
I can't help thinking we'd be
better off if you hadn't escaped.

1147
01:24:56,407 --> 01:24:58,898
That's what you can't help thinking?
Who cares?

1148
01:24:59,077 --> 01:25:01,568
This is a big night.
I ought to be celebrating.

1149
01:25:01,746 --> 01:25:04,738
And that's what I'm gonna do too!
Celebrate. Alone!

1150
01:25:04,916 --> 01:25:09,250
From now on, I'm gonna do everything
alone! I don't need any of you!

1151
01:25:22,433 --> 01:25:24,196
Hey.

1152
01:25:25,203 --> 01:25:26,568
- Yes?
- This stuff's weak.

1153
01:25:26,737 --> 01:25:28,432
- Get me bourbon.
- Sorry, sir...

1154
01:25:28,606 --> 01:25:32,269
...but with the kind of license
we have here, it's against the law.

1155
01:25:32,610 --> 01:25:34,100
All right. Give me a check.

1156
01:25:34,278 --> 01:25:38,510
- I'm sorry, sir, if you feel...
- No. It's all right. It's just, it's too noisy.

1157
01:25:38,716 --> 01:25:40,911
I don't like crowded places.

1158
01:26:03,107 --> 01:26:06,975
<i>Are you planning to do a lot of running</i>
<i>around in this room?</i>

1159
01:26:13,584 --> 01:26:15,211
Have a good time...

1160
01:26:16,220 --> 01:26:18,916
...and bye-bye.

1161
01:26:40,912 --> 01:26:43,005
Come in, mister.

1162
01:26:43,948 --> 01:26:46,109
- What's your pleasure?
- Double bourbon.

1163
01:26:46,284 --> 01:26:48,081
Yes, sir.

1164
01:26:58,129 --> 01:27:01,326
Midnight, and another day.

1165
01:27:06,504 --> 01:27:09,302
Two pages must've got hanged together.

1166
01:27:45,776 --> 01:27:48,745
<i>Do a good job of it!</i>
<i>What does it matter?</i>

1167
01:27:48,913 --> 01:27:52,314
<i>Twenty-two, 23, 25!</i>

1168
01:28:44,201 --> 01:28:46,829
Katherine! Katherine!

1169
01:29:05,523 --> 01:29:10,153
Katherine, don't leave me alone.

1170
01:29:22,073 --> 01:29:24,439
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

1171
01:29:24,608 --> 01:29:27,270
...have you agreed upon a verdict?

1172
01:29:27,478 --> 01:29:28,877
We have, Your Honor.

1173
01:29:29,046 --> 01:29:32,106
You will hand the verdict
to the bailiff.

1174
01:29:39,557 --> 01:29:43,459
We find in the case of the people of
the state versus the defendants...

1175
01:29:43,627 --> 01:29:47,723
...charged with the murder of Joseph
Wilson as set forth in the indictment.

1176
01:29:47,898 --> 01:29:50,025
Jasper Anderson, not guilty.

1177
01:29:51,135 --> 01:29:53,899
Gilbert Clark, not guilty.

1178
01:29:54,071 --> 01:29:57,939
Richard Durkin, guilty.

1179
01:29:58,109 --> 01:30:00,737
Walter Dubbs, guilty.

1180
01:30:00,911 --> 01:30:03,277
Kirby Dawson, guilty.

1181
01:30:03,447 --> 01:30:05,779
Frederick Garrett, guilty.

1182
01:30:05,950 --> 01:30:09,249
- Walter Gordon, guilty.
- No, no! I'm not. Not me!

1183
01:30:09,420 --> 01:30:11,718
Go ahead, go ahead, get it over with!

1184
01:30:30,341 --> 01:30:32,775
Order in the court!

1185
01:30:38,149 --> 01:30:40,481
Your Honor, I am Joseph Wilson.

1186
01:30:40,651 --> 01:30:42,915
Keep your seats!

1187
01:30:44,188 --> 01:30:46,418
- Go on.
- I know that by coming here...

1188
01:30:46,590 --> 01:30:49,616
...I saved the lives of these 22 people.

1189
01:30:49,827 --> 01:30:53,957
But that isn't why I'm here. I don't care
anything about saving them.

1190
01:30:54,165 --> 01:30:58,295
They're murderers. I know the law
says they're not because I'm still alive.

1191
01:30:58,469 --> 01:31:00,130
But that's not their fault.

1192
01:31:00,438 --> 01:31:04,772
And the law doesn't know that a lot of
things that were very important to me...

1193
01:31:04,942 --> 01:31:08,434
...silly things, maybe,
like a belief in justice...

1194
01:31:08,612 --> 01:31:11,706
...and an idea that men were civilized...

1195
01:31:12,349 --> 01:31:17,218
...and a feeling of pride that this country
of mine was different from all others.

1196
01:31:17,388 --> 01:31:21,586
The law doesn't know those things were
burned to death within me that night.

1197
01:31:22,159 --> 01:31:24,320
I came here today for my own sake.

1198
01:31:24,528 --> 01:31:26,393
I couldn't stand it anymore.

1199
01:31:26,597 --> 01:31:30,795
I couldn't stop thinking about them,
with every step and every breath I took.

1200
01:31:30,968 --> 01:31:34,199
And I didn't believe Katherine
when she said...

1201
01:31:36,307 --> 01:31:40,141
Katherine is the young lady
who was going to marry me.

1202
01:31:40,311 --> 01:31:43,644
Maybe someday after
I've paid for what I did...

1203
01:31:43,814 --> 01:31:46,681
...there'll be a chance to begin again.

1204
01:31:47,017 --> 01:31:49,349
And then maybe...

1205
01:31:49,720 --> 01:31:52,348
...Katherine and I...
- Joe.

1206
01:32:26,457 --> 01:32:28,448
[ENGLISH]

